  "description": "The TX22 dataset investigates real-time prediction and management of trust-based decisions in human-automation interaction during simulated semi-automated driving. Using a leader-follower paradigm, this study explores methods to predict instances requiring driver intervention and employs predictive feedback mechanisms to influence trust calibration and support effective joint human-automation system performance in military vehicle operations.",
  "methods_description": "Data were collected during simulated semi-automated driving tasks in a leader-follower paradigm. Participants made trust-based decisions regarding control authority hand-off and take-over, with real-time predictions of intervention necessity and feedback mechanisms designed to support trust management.",
